<span id="freeTextContainer10106085699259346995">Having loved Ruth Ware&apos;s previous books I was looking forward to this one with great anticipation. I was greatly disappointed however. There&apos;s build up, and build up, and more build up. Then we get to the crunch and it&apos;s over in a few pages. The first 320 pages were boring and the last 20 pages were rushed.<br/><br/>Enough said.</span>
  <span id="freeText10106085699259346995" style="display:none">Having loved Ruth Ware's previous books I was looking forward to this one with great anticipation. I was greatly disappointed however. There's build up, and build up, and more build up. Then we get to the crunch and it's over in a few pages. The first 320 pages were boring and the last 20 pages were rushed.<br /><br />Enough said.</span>
