<div class='bookAuthorProfile__about'>

<span id="freeTextContainer11541208080153664008">Ruth Ware grew up in Sussex, on the south coast of England. After graduating from Manchester University she moved to Paris, before settling in North London. She has worked as a waitress, a bookseller, a teacher of English as a foreign language and a press officer. She is married with two small children, and In a Dark, Dark Wood is her début thriller.<br/><br/>Find her on twitter at <a target='_blank' rel='noopener nofollow' href='http://www.twitter.com/ruthwarewriter'>www.twitter.com/ruthwarew</a></span>
  <span id="freeText11541208080153664008" style="display:none">Ruth Ware grew up in Sussex, on the south coast of England. After graduating from Manchester University she moved to Paris, before settling in North London. She has worked as a waitress, a bookseller, a teacher of English as a foreign language and a press officer. She is married with two small children, and In a Dark, Dark Wood is her début thriller.<br /><br />Find her on twitter at <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://www.twitter.com/ruthwarewriter">www.twitter.com/ruthwarewriter</a>, on facebook at <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://www.facebook.com/ruthwarewriter">www.facebook.com/ruthwarewriter</a> or via her website - <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://www.ruthware.com">www.ruthware.com</a> </span>
